did.unittitle: Department of Athletics, Yale University, records documenting football

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of scrapbooks, memorabilia, correspondence, coaches files and manuals, a ledger, and printed material documenting football at Yale, including George D. Vaill's "Instructions to Competitors" and a videotape of a NBC Nightly News segment concerning the 100th Yale-Harvard football game. Records of coaches Paul L. Veeder and Carm Coza are also included.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 38-B (YRG 38-B), Records documenting specific sports at Yale.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is partially restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Department of Athletics, Yale University, Records Documenting Football (RU 141). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of scrapbooks, memorabilia, correspondence, coaches files and manuals, a ledger, and printed material documenting football at Yale, including George D. Vaill's "Instructions to Competitors" and a videotape of a NBC Nightly News segment concerning the 100th Yale-Harvard football game. Records of coaches Paul L. Veeder and Carm Coza are also included.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy of non-commercially produced items for their personal use should consult the ordering reproductions information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.

did.unittitle: Leo Stoutsenberger cartoons created for the Yale Football Newsletter

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Leo Stoutsenberger was a professor at the Paier College of Art in Hamden, CT. He rendered several comic strip narratives of Yale football games during the latter half of the 20th Century.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Depicts actio of 18 November 1972, during Yale Football's centennial season. Of paticular note is Dick Jauron, who went on to play professionally for the Detroit Lions, and was later head coach fo the Chicago Bears.
